  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">End Child, Early and Forced marriage for girls in Katsina State, Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In rural Northern Nigeria almost half of all girls are married to older men, usually against their will, by the age of 15. These girls then have to leave school early, and they face a variety of health hazards, especially in relation to childbirth. This grant allows a well-established local Non Governmental Organisation (NGO) to undertake research on this issue, including extensive consultations with women themselves, and local leaders. This research will then be used to help prepare a detailed proposal which focuses on the best ways of tackling this problem.</narrative>
  </description>
